page.title: 12HOUSING IN SELSEY
page.content: There are about 1300 houses in Selsey.There are different kinds of houses.In the West there are mostly caravans.The few houses are detached,semi_detached,bungalows and terraced. The walls are mostly brick often with pebble_dash mainly tiled roofs with some thatched. In the centre there are mainly semi_detached, bungalows, terraced and flats for old people.The walls are brick, cement or stone and pebble_dash. The roofs are tiled or slate, some thatched. Most houses have gardens but not the flats.Old houses have chimneys but not all new houses. In the East the houses have been mostly built in the last twenty years, mainly bungalows also semi_detached, town houses and terraced houses. Most have brick walls and roofs are nearly all tiles,some houses were once railway carriages.
